params.inputAmountSent: The amount of `inputToken` that was sent to `IOrderBookV4OrderTaker`.
params.inputToken: The token that was sent to `IOrderBookV4OrderTaker`.
params.outputToken: The token that `IOrderBookV4` will attempt to pull from `IOrderBookV4OrderTaker` after this callback returns.
params.takeOrdersData: The data passed to `takeOrders` by the caller.
params.totalOutputAmount: The total amount of `outputToken` that `IOrderBookV4` will attempt to pull from `IOrderBookV4OrderTaker` after this callback returns.

supportsInterface(bytes4).details: Returns true if this contract implements the interface defined by `interfaceId`. See the corresponding https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-165#how-interfaces-are-identified[EIP section] to learn more about how these ids are created. This function call must use less than 30 000 gas.

onTakeOrders(address,address,uint256,uin.notice: Called by `IOrderBookV4` when `takeOrders` is called with non-zero data, if it caused a non-zero input amount. I.e. if the order(s) taker received some tokens. Input and output directions are relative to the `IOrderBookV4OrderTaker` contract. If the order(s) taker had an active debt from a flash loan then that debt will be paid _before_ calculating any input amounts sent. i.e. the debt is deducted from the input amount before this callback is called.
